name	setting	description
DateStyle	ISO, MDY	Sets the display format for date and time values.
IntervalStyle	postgres	Sets the display format for interval values.
TimeZone	Etc/UTC	Sets the time zone for displaying and interpreting time stamps.
__delta_only_variant_encoding_enabled	off	Enables the Parquet reader to identify a Variant structurally.
access_mode	automatic	Access mode of the database (AUTOMATIC, READ_ONLY or READ_WRITE)
allocator_background_threads	off	Whether to enable the allocator background thread.
allocator_bulk_deallocation_flush_threshold	512.0 MiB	If a bulk deallocation larger than this occurs, flush outstanding allocations.
allocator_flush_threshold	128.0 MiB	Peak allocation threshold at which to flush the allocator after completing a task.
allow_asterisks_in_http_paths	off	Allow '*' character in URLs users can query
allow_community_extensions	on	Allow to load community built extensions
allow_extensions_metadata_mismatch	off	Allow to load extensions with not compatible metadata
allow_parser_override_extension	DEFAULT	Allow extensions to override the current parser
allow_persistent_secrets	on	Allow the creation of persistent secrets, that are stored and loaded on restarts
allow_unredacted_secrets	off	Allow printing unredacted secrets
allow_unsigned_extensions	off	Allow to load extensions with invalid or missing signatures
allowed_configs	[]	List of configuration options that are ALWAYS allowed to be changed - even when lock_configuration is true
allowed_directories	[]	List of directories/prefixes that are ALWAYS allowed to be queried - even when enable_external_access is false
allowed_paths	[]	List of files that are ALWAYS allowed to be queried - even when enable_external_access is false
application_name	(empty)	Sets the application name to be reported in statistics and logs.
arrow_large_buffer_size	off	Whether Arrow buffers for strings, blobs, uuids and bits should be exported using large buffers
arrow_lossless_conversion	off	Whenever a DuckDB type does not have a clear native or canonical extension match in Arrow, export the types with a duckdb.type_name extension name.
arrow_output_list_view	off	Whether export to Arrow format should use ListView as the physical layout for LIST columns
arrow_output_version	1.0	Whether strings should be produced by DuckDB in Utf8View format instead of Utf8
asof_loop_join_threshold	64	The maximum number of rows we need on the left side of an ASOF join to use a nested loop join
auto_checkpoint_skip_wal_threshold	100000	The estimated WAL write size at which point we will skip writing to the WAL and only checkpoint. Skipping writing to the WAL means concurrent commits are blocked while the checkpoint is happening.
auto_fallback_to_full_download	on	Allows automatically falling back to full file downloads when possible.
autoinstall_extension_repository	(empty)	Overrides the custom endpoint for extension installation on autoloading
autoinstall_known_extensions	off	Whether known extensions are allowed to be automatically installed when a query depends on them
autoload_known_extensions	off	Whether known extensions are allowed to be automatically loaded when a query depends on them
binary_as_string	off	In Parquet files, interpret binary data as a string.
block_allocator_memory	0 bytes	Physical memory that the block allocator is allowed to use (this memory is never freed and cannot be reduced).
bytea_output	hex	Sets the output format for bytea.
ca_cert_file	(empty)	Path to a custom certificate file for self-signed certificates.
catalog_error_max_schemas	100	The maximum number of schemas the system will scan for "did you mean..." style errors in the catalog
checkpoint_on_detach	DEFAULT	Override checkpoint behavior when detaching a database. ENABLED always checkpoints, DISABLED never checkpoints, DEFAULT defers to the global checkpoint_on_shutdown setting.
checkpoint_threshold	16.0 MiB	The WAL size threshold at which to automatically trigger a checkpoint (e.g. 1GB)
cleanup_interval_step	1	Number of commit ticks between background unreferenced-file cleanup passes for newly created inverted indexes. Per-index WITH (cleanup_interval_step = ...) overrides. 0 disables cleanup. Default: 1.
client_encoding	UTF8	Sets the client's character set encoding.
client_min_messages	notice	Sets the message levels that are sent to the client.
compaction_interval	1000	Background compaction interval (ms) for newly created inverted indexes. Per-index WITH (compaction_interval = ...) overrides. 0 disables the compaction task. Default: 1000.
configure_metrics	[*]	Accepts a JSON enabling custom metrics
configure_profiling	[*]	Accepts a JSON enabling custom metrics
current_transaction_invalidation_policy	STANDARD_POLICY	Which types of exceptions invalidate the database for the current transaction
custom_extension_repository	(empty)	Overrides the custom endpoint for remote extension installation
custom_profiling_settings	[*]	Accepts a JSON enabling custom metrics
custom_user_agent	(empty)	Metadata from DuckDB callers
debug_asof_iejoin	off	DEBUG SETTING: force use of IEJoin to implement AsOf joins
debug_checkpoint_abort	NONE	DEBUG SETTING: trigger an abort while checkpointing for testing purposes
debug_checkpoint_sleep_ms	0	DEBUG SETTING: time to sleep before a checkpoint
debug_disable_optimizer	off	DEBUG SETTING: disable optimizer for most queries
debug_eviction_queue_sleep_micro_seconds	0	DEBUG SETTING: time for the eviction queue to sleep before acquiring shared ownership of block memory
debug_force_external	off	DEBUG SETTING: force out-of-core computation for operators that support it, used for testing
debug_force_fetch_row	off	DEBUG SETTING: force per-row fetching during scans, used for testing
debug_force_no_cross_product	off	DEBUG SETTING: Force disable cross product generation when hyper graph isn't connected, used for testing
debug_physical_table_scan_execution_strategy	DEFAULT	DEBUG SETTING: force use of given strategy for executing physical table scans
debug_skip_checkpoint_on_commit	off	DEBUG SETTING: skip checkpointing on commit
debug_verification_mode	NONE	DEBUG SETTING: toggle the verification mode.
debug_verification_projection	off	DEBUG SETTING: add internal verification projections to stress optimizers
debug_verify_blocks	off	DEBUG SETTING: verify block metadata during checkpointing
debug_verify_column_bindings	off	DEBUG SETTING: run extra internal verification of column bindings
debug_verify_serializer	off	DEBUG SETTING: verify logical plan serializer
debug_verify_statement	NONE	DEBUG SETTING: the type of statement verification to perform
debug_verify_stats	off	DEBUG SETTING: verify statistics are correct during execution, instead of assuming
debug_verify_vector	NONE	DEBUG SETTING: enable vector verification
debug_window_mode	WINDOW	DEBUG SETTING: switch window mode to use
default_block_size	262144	The default block size for new duckdb database files (new as-in, they do not yet exist).
default_collation	(empty)	The collation setting used when none is specified
default_null_order	NULLS_LAST	NULL ordering used when none is specified (NULLS_FIRST or NULLS_LAST)
default_order	ASCENDING	The order type used when none is specified (ASC or DESC)
default_secret_storage	local_file	Allows switching the default storage for secrets
default_transaction_invalidation_policy	ALL_ERRORS_INVALIDATE_TRANSACTION	When to invalidate transactions when errors occur (SYNTACTIC_ERRORS_DO_NOT_INVALIDATE, i.e. parser and binder exceptions do not invalidate, or ALL_ERRORS_INVALIDATE_TRANSACTION)
default_transaction_isolation	repeatable read	Sets the transaction isolation level of each new transaction.
default_transaction_read_only	off	Sets the default read-only status of new transactions.
deprecated_using_key_syntax	DEFAULT	Configures the use of the deprecated union syntax for USING KEY CTEs.
disable_database_invalidation	on	Disables invalidating the database instance when encountering a fatal error. Should be used with great care, as DuckDB cannot guarantee correct behavior after a fatal error.
disable_parquet_prefetching	off	Disable the prefetching mechanism in Parquet
disable_timestamptz_casts	off	Disable casting from timestamp to timestamptz 
disabled_compression_methods	(empty)	Disable a specific set of compression methods (comma separated)
disabled_filesystems	(empty)	Disable specific file systems preventing access (e.g. LocalFileSystem)
disabled_log_types	<slt:ignore>	Sets the list of disabled loggers
disabled_optimizers	(empty)	DEBUG SETTING: disable a specific set of optimizers (comma separated)
duckdb_api	cpp	DuckDB API surface
dynamic_or_filter_threshold	50	The maximum amount of OR filters we generate dynamically from a hash join
enable_caching_operators	on	Enables caching operators that cache intermediate results
enable_curl_server_cert_verification	on	Enable server side certificate verification for CURL backend.
enable_external_access	on	Allow the database to access external state (through e.g. loading/installing modules, COPY TO/FROM, CSV readers, pandas replacement scans, etc)
enable_external_file_cache	on	Allow the database to cache external files (e.g., Parquet) in memory.
enable_fsst_vectors	off	Allow scans on FSST compressed segments to emit compressed vectors to utilize late decompression
enable_geoparquet_conversion	on	Attempt to decode/encode geometry data in/as GeoParquet files if the spatial extension is present.
enable_global_s3_configuration	on	Automatically fetch AWS credentials from environment variables.
enable_http_logging	on	(deprecated) Enables HTTP logging
enable_http_metadata_cache	off	Whether or not the global http metadata is used to cache HTTP metadata
enable_logging	<slt:ignore>	Enables the logger
enable_macro_dependencies	off	Enable created MACROs to create dependencies on the referenced objects (such as tables)
enable_object_cache	off	[PLACEHOLDER] Legacy setting - does nothing
enable_profiling	NULL	Enables profiling, and sets the output format (JSON, QUERY_TREE, QUERY_TREE_OPTIMIZER)
enable_progress_bar	off	Enables the progress bar, printing progress to the terminal for long queries
enable_progress_bar_print	on	Controls the printing of the progress bar, when 'enable_progress_bar' is true
enable_server_cert_verification	off	Enable server side certificate verification.
enable_view_dependencies	off	Enable created VIEWs to create dependencies on the referenced objects (such as tables)
enabled_log_types	(empty)	Sets the list of enabled loggers
errors_as_json	off	Output error messages as structured JSON instead of as a raw string
experimental_metadata_reuse	on	EXPERIMENTAL: Re-use row group and table metadata when checkpointing.
explain_output	PHYSICAL_ONLY	Output of EXPLAIN statements (ALL, OPTIMIZED_ONLY, PHYSICAL_ONLY)
extension_directories	[]	Set the directories to store extensions in
